THE funeral service of the late former Baroka FC and Tshakhuma Tsha Madzivhandila FC star player Khunadi Nkoana are as follows: The funeral will be held at Ga-Semenya in Limpopo on Sunday 12 July, at 7am. The 28 year-old Nkoana passed away this past Tuesday after complaining of stomach pains. Many Mzansi diski fanatics will remember Nkoana for his delicious diski when he turned out for Baroka FC against Kaizer Chiefs in the 2011 Nedbank Cup. The well-travelled star is also a former Black Leopards FC player as well. Nkoana was in the books of Magesi FC when Coronavirus forced the league to be suspended. MAY HIS SOUL REST IN ETERNAL PEACE 